level of wealth gets lower. We call this a ‘counterclockwise concavification’ to capture
the sense that at any specific level of wealth, one can think of the increase in the MPC
at lower levels of wealth as being a counterclockwise rotation of the lower portion of the
consumption function around that level of wealth.
