Lemma 4. (A Counterclockwise Concavification Increases Prudence.)
Consider an agent who has a utility function with u0 > 0, u00 < 0, u000 ≥ 0, and nonincreasing absolute prudence (−u000 /u00 ). If c(w) is concave and ĉ(w) is a counterclockwise
